Steve Fossett's attempt at a solo, non-stop flight around the world faced challenges due to the jet stream's unpredictable movements.
The delicate aircraft relies on prevailing winds for propulsion, making turbulence a major concern.
Despite equipment failures, including a GPS malfunction, Fossett remains optimistic.
The mission, funded by Virgin Atlantic, aims to advance aviation technology and inspire interest in exploration.
Fossett's journey will test his endurance and piloting skills, with support from a chase plane and ground crew.
As he embarks on this historic adventure, Fossett's determination and passion for aviation shine through.
